The President has confirmed Michael Froman as the United States Trade Representative. Froman has been a close advisor to the President on international economic issues and will continue to play a key role on the economic team. He is trusted and respected by partners around the world and has been instrumental in advancing the international economic agenda. In his new position, Froman will prioritize promoting growth, creating jobs, and strengthening the middle class. He will also work to open new markets for American businesses, ensure fair competition for American workers, farmers, and ranchers, and enforce trade rights.